{"word":"δάψιλδε","slug":"δάψιλδε","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n23597\" key=\"da/yilde\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"suff\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">δάψιλ-δε</orth>, an enclitic post-position: joined, <sense n=\"I\" id=\"n23597.0\" level=\"2\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> to names of Places in the acc., to denote <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">motion towards</tr_> that place, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">οἶκόνδε</foreign> (<gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Att.\">Att.</a></gram> </gramGrp> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">οἴκαδε</foreign>) home-<tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">wards,</tr_> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἅλαδε</foreign> sea-<tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">wards,</tr_> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Οὔλυμπόνδε</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">to</tr_> Olympus, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Αἴγυπτόνδε</foreign> to the Nile, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">θύραζε</foreign> (for <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">θύρασδε</foreign>) <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">to</tr_> the door (v. sub vocc.); repeated with the possess. Pron., <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὅνδε δόμονδε</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:16:445\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">16.445</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; sts. after <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">εἰς, εἰς ἅλαδε</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:10:351\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">10.351</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; after the gen. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Ἄϊδόσδε.</foreign> </sense> <sense n=\"b\" id=\"n23597.1\" level=\"4\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> to names of persons, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">Πηλεΐωνάδε</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:24:338\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">24.338</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; to Prons., <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἡμέτερόνδε, ὑμ-,</foreign> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:8:39\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">8.39</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:23:86\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">23.86</biblScope> </bibl>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὅνδε,</foreign> <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.</abbr> supr. In <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Att.\">Att.</a></gram> </gramGrp> mostly joined to the names of places, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Ἐλευσῖνάδε,</foreign> etc.; also <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Ἀθήναζε, Θήβαζε</foreign> (for <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Ἀθήνασδε, Θήβασδε</foreign>); rarely, in <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Att.\">Att.</a></gram></gramGrp>, with appellatives, as <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">οἴκαδε.</foreign> </sense> <sense n=\"c\" id=\"n23597.2\" level=\"4\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> to time-words, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">βουλυτόνδε</foreign> (v. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">βουλυτός</foreign>). </sense> <sense n=\"2\" id=\"n23597.3\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> to denote <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">purpose</tr_> only, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">μήτι φόβονδ᾽ ἀγόρευε</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:5:252\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">5.252</biblScope></bibl></cit>. </sense> <sense n=\"II\" id=\"n23597.4\" level=\"2\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> to the demonstr. Pron., to give it greater force, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὅδε, τοιόσδε, τοσόσδε,</foreign> etc., such a man <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">as this</tr_> (v. sub vocc.).</sense> </entryFree>"}]}